com.cornell.opencomm.client
Class XMPPClient

java.lang.Object
  Activity
      com.cornell.opencomm.client.XMPPClient

public class XMPPClient
extends Activity

Main Android Activity Class for the XMPPClient implementation. This class is the point of entry of the XMPPClient application. This class is responsible for registering various Presence, Packet and Invitation listeners. It is also responsible for registering and defining the onClick activity for various buttons on the main screen of the GUI of the XMPPClient.

Author:
Abhishek

setConnection

public void setConnection(org.jivesoftware.smack.XMPPConnection connection)
Convenience method to allow accessibility to the XMPPConnection object that represents the connection with the Jabber server. Called by Settings dialog when a connection is establised with the Jabber server. Once a connection is established, listeners for Invitation and peer-2-peer or MUC chat are registered in this method.

Parameters:
connection - the XMPPConnection that represents jabber connection
